Conditional branching.

```r
if (condition) {
  # true branch
} else {
  # false branch
}
```

Alternative branch in `if` statement.

```r
if (x > 0) {
  print("positive")
} else {
  print("non-positive")
}
```

Iterate over elements of a vector.

```r
for (i in 1:10) {
  print(i)
}

for (item in my_list) {
  cat(item, "\n")
}
```

Execute a block while a condition is TRUE.

```r
while (x > 0) {
  x <- x - 1
}
```

Exit the current `for`, `while`, or `repeat` loop.

```r
for (i in 1:100) {
  if (i > 10) break
}
```

Explicitly return a value from a function.

```r
my_func <- function(x) {
  if (x < 0) return(NULL)
  sqrt(x)
}
```

Generate a sequence `1, 2, ..., length(x)`.

```r
for (i in seq_along(x)) {
  cat(i, x[i], "\n")
}
```

Handle errors and conditions.

```r
result <- tryCatch({
  log(-1)
}, warning = function(w) {
  message("Warning: ", w$message)
}, error = function(e) {
  message("Error: ", e$message)
  NA
}, finally = {
  cat("Done\n")
})
```

Define an S4 method for a generic.

```r
setMethod("greet", "Person", function(object) {
  cat("Hello,", object@name, "\n")
})
```

Standard for loop iterating over a sequence.

```r
for (i in 1:n) {
  # body
}
```

While loop.

```r
while (condition) {
  # body
}
```

Define a named function.

```r
my_func <- function(x, y = 1) {
  x + y
}
```

Full if/else if/else block.

```r
if (cond1) {
  # ...
} else if (cond2) {
  # ...
} else {
  # ...
}
```

Error handling block.

```r
tryCatch({
  # risky code
}, error = function(e) {
  message(e$message)
})
```

